      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ETERNALLY YOURS (3) got the maiden win out of the way last start with a 1.2L victory when running over the top from midfield. Back to 1500m today shouldn't pose too much of an issue. Looks to get every chance here today from the draw and he can repeat the dose in this suitable assignment. DIABLO LAD (2) has been beaten narrowly in his past couple, missing by 0.8L last start and 0.6L the start prior at this track and trip. Fiore rides now and he's on the cusp of ending his 800-day win drought. Can go one better now. WIN TO RETIRE (9) has been racing consistently including a last start third over 1600m at this track, beaten 1.5 lengths. Likely to be about the mark again. KAMAKAZI SHOOTER (5) finished 3 lengths away in fifth last time out over 1100m at this track after being in contention on the corner eight days ago. Steps up in distance today. Among the chances. PETITE VITESSE (10) won't be far away.",
